    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-06-24T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-06-24T05:00:00-05:00" n="555"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d555">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/14748: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-06-24T19:00:00+09:00"
                            >June 24, 1941—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received June 24—9:45 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>874. Embassy’s 872, June 24, 4 p.m. Wang-Konoye statement. It is believed that
                    the statement concerning mutual defense against communism were inserted at
                    Wang’s insistence, as he was perturbed by Japan’s apparent <hi rend="italic"
                        >rapprochement</hi> with the Soviet Union. As expected, the Japanese
                    Government promised to assist toward extending the authority of the Nanking
                    régime, but specific plans were not mentioned despite a suggestion that their
                    promising would result in winning the confidence of the people.</p>
                <p>Sent to the Department via Shanghai. Shanghai please repeat to Chungking, Nanking
                    and Peiping.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
